title: Episode 37: Celebrating Student Research... 2017 Edition
itunes:author: UW-Green Bay Psychology Department
itunes:summary: In this episode, Annemarie Schwery and Allee Schramm interview five different students about their research on topics related to stigma, exercise, parental attention and more. These six students (Michelle McChesney, Allee Schramm, Annemarie Schwery, Katrina Weber, Kennedy Wendt) represent just a few of the more than 35 UWGB Psychology students who will be presenting their work at the Midwestern Psychological Association Conference.
